node.text: The moment the Dallas Cowboys used their first-round pick on Penn St. LB Micah Parsons, 📹 @nflfilms.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schefter on August 23, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and people playing football.

node.text: Jaguars’ rookie RB Travis Etienne was spotted postgame in a walking boot, limping due to his left foot injury. Etienne suffered a mid-foot sprain Monday night at New Orleans, per source. It’s expected to sideline him indefinitely and require further testing.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schefter on August 23, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and playing football.

node.text: Josh Rosen is signing with the Atlanta Falcons, per @jordanschultz. Atlanta lost AJ McCarron to a torn ACL on Saturday, leaving Matt Ryan and Felipe Franks as the only healthy QBs on Atlanta’s roster. Atlanta will be Rosen’s fifth NFL team after stints in Arizona, Miami, Tampa Bay, San Francisco and now the Falcons.

node.text: Saints’ TE Adam Trautman was carted to the locker room with an ankle/foot injury.

node.text: Rams RB Darrell Henderson left practice today with what tests show is a mildly sprained thumb that is not expected to keep him out of the regular-season opener vs. the Bears, per source. Rams already had lost RBs Cam Akers (Achilles) and Raymond Calais (foot) to season-ending injuries.

node.text: Pats’ QB Cam Newton out five days due to COVID protocols. Pats: “Due to a misunderstanding about tests conducted away from NFL facilities, and as required by the NFL-NFLPA protocols, Cam will be subject to the five-day entry cadence process before returning to the facility..."
